{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c1aff1e2-9f0e-48cb-97fe-d46565472fc9","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_hdJurFAD5zgwTbPRAYCDAA","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing crash dump config"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_GQUeS6HioXu90H0odSmDCE","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"echo \"Reference check for .NET NativeAOT crash dump env vars\"","description":"Quick reference","initial_wait":5},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Quick reference"}],"interactionId":"8a518cef-837d-4a3a-974d-d7d19e0ddb64","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. I need to provide:\n\n1. The environment variables needed to configure .NET to use createdump for automatic crash dump collection\n2. The Kubernetes pod spec changes (volume mounts, etc.) to collect the dumps\n\nFor NativeAOT .NET apps, crash dump collection works differently than CoreCLR. In NativeAOT, you need to set specific environment variables to enable crash dump generation. The key environment variables are:\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` to enable crash dumps\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` to specify the dump type (Mini, Heap, Triage, or Full)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` to define where dumps get written\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` for diagnostics during dump creation\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` pointing to the createdump tool since it's in a non-standard location\n\nFor Kubernetes, I need to show how to mount volumes for the dumps and configure the pod spec with these environment variables.","outputTokens":502,"requestId":"C3C2:2EAB99:1BE486A:1F80D61:6A07C257"},"id":"5abc4c2b-2fd0-4323-9612-b4d59de27b96","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:03:29.460Z","parentId":"d130b5ce-5466-4676-aa93-2a8d55de4dbc"}
