{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba6a0556-9356-40e9-89b4-6bbe48d18021","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT on .NET 11:\n\n**Environment variables** (on your container):\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"            # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/dumps/core_%t_%p\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes** — add a writable volume for dumps:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      # ... your existing container config ...\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/dumps/core_%t_%p\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /dumps\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]   # required by createdump\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi          # adjust to your app's memory footprint\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to read process memory.\n- **`%t`** = timestamp, **`%p`** = PID in the dump filename.\n- Use `emptyDir` for ephemeral collection (pair with a sidecar or CronJob to ship dumps to persistent storage), or swap in a PVC if you need persistence across pod restarts.\n- For NativeAOT specifically, the dump will contain native frames; load it with `lldb` (not `dotnet-dump`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8a518cef-837d-4a3a-974d-d7d19e0ddb64","outputTokens":552,"requestId":"C3D8:C525B:1BF93D6:1F8CA62:6A07C261"},"id":"9816ff70-63b3-4498-a971-ee1374220144","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:03:40.097Z","parentId":"1b621ab1-c0fb-4f9f-a717-dfbda505b92f"}
